1. What is the purpose of links in Markdown?

A. Styling text
B. Connecting to external resources
C. Writing code
D. Creating lists

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Links connect your document to external documentation or resources, improving usability and context.

2. What is the purpose of images in Markdown?

A. Styling
B. Visualization
C. Code execution
D. Debugging

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Images help visualize concepts like architecture or workflows.

3. Which syntax is used for links?

A.

B. text

C. (text)[url]
D. <text>(url)

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Standard link syntax is [text](url).

4. Which syntax is used for images?

A. text

B.

C. (alt)[url]
D. <img>(url)

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Images use ![alt text](url) syntax.

5. What distinguishes images from links?

A. #
B. !
C. *
D. -

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: The ! prefix indicates an image instead of a link.

🔗 Links Best Practices
6. Good link text should be:

A. “Click here”
B. “Link”
C. Descriptive
D. Random

✅ Answer: C
📘 Explanation: Descriptive text improves clarity and usability.

7. Bare URLs like https://example.com are:

A. Recommended
B. Best practice
C. Poor practice
D. Required

✅ Answer: C
📘 Explanation: Use proper [text](url) format instead of raw URLs.

8. Links should:

A. Be vague
B. Be descriptive
C. Be long
D. Be hidden

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Clear link text helps both humans and AI.

9. Links improve:

A. Speed
B. Context
C. UI
D. Storage

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: They provide reference context for understanding.

10. Example of correct link:

A. https://docs.python.org

B. Python Docs

C. (Python Docs)https://docs.python.org

D. <Python Docs>

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Proper syntax includes text + URL.

🖼️ Images Best Practices
11. Alt text is:

A. Optional decoration
B. Description of image
C. URL
D. Title

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Alt text describes what the image shows.

12. Good alt text should:

A. Be vague
B. Be descriptive
C. Be short only
D. Be random

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Helps accessibility and AI understanding.

13. Example of good alt text:

A. Image
B. Screenshot
C. Data flow diagram showing user → app → API
D. Picture

✅ Answer: C
📘 Explanation: Describes what the image shows, not just its type.

14. Image syntax includes:

A. #
B. !
C. *
D. &

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: ! is mandatory for images.

15. Images improve:

A. Code execution
B. Visualization
C. Speed
D. Storage

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Visual aids enhance understanding.

