A. Title
B. Architecture section
C. Footer
D. Code

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Images often explain system design.

21. Relative image path example:

A. https://image.png

B. ./images/diagram.png
C. image
D. diagram

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Relative paths link to local project files.

⚠️ Common Mistakes
22. Missing ! in image syntax:

A. Correct
B. Creates image
C. Creates link
D. Error

✅ Answer: C
📘 Explanation: Without !, it becomes a link instead of image.

23. Using vague alt text leads to:

A. Better output
B. AI confusion
C. Faster speed
D. Optimization

✅ Answer: B
📘 Explanation: Poor descriptions reduce clarity.

24. Using raw URLs instead of markdown links:

A. Good
B. Best
C. Bad practice
D. Required

✅ Answer: C
📘 Explanation: Proper syntax improves readability.

25. Proper use of links & images results in:

A. Poor AI output
B. Better documentation and AI understanding
C. Errors
